                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d73">
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-chapter-head">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexican call for discovery</hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of Mexico</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-08-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 12, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Acting Secretary</hi>: By direction of my Government,
                    and in accordance with Article IV of the protocol of arbitration between the
                    Republic of Mexico and the United States of America for the settlement of
                    certain questions arisen in regard to the so-called “Pious Fund of the
                    Californias,” signed on May 22, 1902, I ask that there be made known to the
                    Government of Mexico, as part of its evidence, the following facts and
                    documents: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Whether the bishops of California received the sum of $904,700.79
                            Mexican gold, referred to in Mixed Commission’s decision of November 11,
                            1875.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>To what purpose the said sum was applied.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Before whom were the accounts of expenditure rendered.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>What are the documents in which the said accounts are recorded that
                            are to be exhibited hereafter.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>I have to say, in addition, that the foregoing request is understood to be
                    without prejudice to such as may be presented later regarding other facts and
                    documents appertaining to the subject-matter.</p>
                <p>I take pleasure, etc.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">José F. Godoy.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>His Excellency <hi rend="smallcaps">A. A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Etc., etc., etc.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
